fuso no dia a dia.\n- **Notes:** Shark definiu o agente como SharkMain, CEO da estrutura/ecossistema de agentes e da empresa. Prioridade inicial: configurar ferramentas e parear Telegram.\n\n## Context\n\nShark quer começar configurando as ferramentas e o pareamento do Telegram.\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.5","usage":{"input":9019,"output":616,"cacheRead":1536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11171,"cost":{"input":0.045095,"output":0.01848,"cacheRead":0.000768,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.06434300000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778719971027,"responseId":"resp_094b6994f4566fc6016a051ce4b18c819481a3c7fdd4c11424"}}
{"type":"message","id":"07c97d57","parentId":"49692eff","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:53:05.081Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_n2u1zbo95mnIdrNKtKs4B0lB|fc_094b6994f4566fc6016a051cf08a58819499f4b696346b8cf8","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/progress-drafts.md:87:Discord and Telegram, `streaming.mode: \"block\"` is still preview streaming, not\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/progress-drafts.md:278:| Telegram        | Send one message, then edit it.        | Older visible drafts may be replaced so final timestamps stay useful. |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/progress-drafts.md:316:explicit reply targets, old Telegram drafts, missing Slack thread targets,\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/progress-drafts.md:326:**Teams behaves differently from Discord or Telegram.**\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/progress-drafts.md:331:used by Discord and Telegram.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/progress-drafts.md:342:- [Telegram](/channels/telegram)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/mantis.md:536:- Telegram: group mention gating, commands, reactions where available.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-runtimes.md:22:| Channel       | Telegram, Discord, Slack, WhatsApp    | Where messages enter and leave OpenClaw.                            |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-runtimes.md:207:- A channel label such as Telegram or Discord tells you where the conversation is happening.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/features.md:12:    Discord, iMessage, Signal, Slack, Telegram, WhatsApp, WebChat, and more with a single Gateway.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/features.md:35:- Built-in channels include Discord, Google Chat, iMessage (legacy), IRC, Signal, Slack, Telegram, WebChat, and WhatsApp\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:99:    - Telegram: one bot per agent via BotFather, copy each token.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:106:    See channel guides: [Discord](/channels/discord), [Telegram](/channels/telegram), [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:263:- `whatsapp`, `telegram`, `discord`, `slack`, `signal`, `imessage`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:326:  <Accordion title=\"Telegram bots per agent\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:336:        { agentId: \"main\", match: { channel: \"telegram\", accountId: \"default\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:337:        { agentId: \"alerts\", match: { channel: \"telegram\", accountId: \"alerts\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:340:        telegram: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:358:    - Tokens live in `channels.telegram.accounts.<id>.botToken` (default account can use `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:438:  <Tab title=\"WhatsApp daily + Telegram deep work\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:439:    Split by channel: route WhatsApp to a fast everyday agent and Telegram to an Opus agent.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:461:        { agentId: \"opus\", match: { channel: \"telegram\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-matrix.md:132:Matrix is one of three live transport lanes (Matrix, Telegram, Discord) that share a single contract checklist defined in [QA overview → Live transport coverage](/concepts/qa-e2e-automation#live-transport-coverage). `qa-channel` remains the broad synthetic suite and is intentionally not part of that matrix.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:13:- **Preview streaming (Telegram/Discord/Slack):** update a temporary **preview message** while generating.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:65:notes or files on channels such as Telegram when an agent emits `MEDIA:` during\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:108:- **Stream chunks:** `blockStreamingDefault: \"on\"` + `blockStreamingBreak: \"text_end\"` (emit as you go). Non-Telegram channels also need `*.blockStreaming: true`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:131:such as Discord and Telegram. It does not enable channel block delivery there.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:141:| Telegram   | ✅    | ✅        | ✅      | editable progress draft |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:154:- Telegram: legacy `streamMode` and scalar/boolean `streaming` values are detected and migrated by doctor/config compatibility paths to `streaming.mode`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:160:Telegram:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:163:- Sends a fresh final message instead of editing in place when a preview has been visible for about one minute, then cleans up the preview so Telegram's timestamp reflects reply completion.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:164:- Preview streaming is skipped when Telegram block streaming is explicitly enabled (to avoid double-streaming).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:200:- **Discord**, **Slack**, **Telegram**, and **Matrix** stream tool-progress into the live preview edit by default when preview streaming is active. Microsoft Teams uses its native progress stream in personal chats.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:201:- Telegram has shipped with tool-progress preview updates enabled since `v2026.4.22`; keeping them enabled preserves that released behavior.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:203:- Tool-progress edits follow the active preview streaming mode; they are skipped when preview streaming is `off` or when block streaming has taken over the message. On Telegram, `streaming.mode: \"off\"` is final-only: generic progress chatter is also suppressed instead of being delivered as standalone status messages, while approval prompts, media payloads, and errors still route normally.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:204:- To keep preview streaming but hide tool-progress lines, set `streaming.preview.toolProgress` to `false` for that channel. To keep tool-progress lines visible while hiding command/exec text, set `streaming.preview.commandText` to `\"status\"` or `streaming.progress.commandText` to `\"status\"`; the default is `\"raw\"` to preserve released behavior. This policy is shared by draft/progress channels that use OpenClaw's compact progress renderer, including Discord, Matrix, Microsoft Teams, Mattermost, Slack draft previews, and Telegram. To disable preview edits entirely, set `streaming.mode` to `off`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:205:- Telegram selected quote replies are an exception: when `replyToMode` is not `\"off\"` and selected quote text is present, OpenClaw skips the answer preview stream for that turn so tool-progress preview lines cannot render. Current-message replies without selected quote text still keep preview streaming. See [Telegram channel docs](/channels/telegram) for details.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:212:    \"telegram\": {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:230:    \"telegram\": {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:48:| `qa telegram`                                       | Live transport lane against a real private Telegram group.                                                                                                                                   |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:114:For transport-real Telegram, Discord, and Slack smoke lanes:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:117:pnpm openclaw qa telegram\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:122:They target a pre-existing real channel with two bots (driver + SUT). Required env vars, scenario lists, output artifacts, and the Convex credential pool are documented in [Telegram, Discord, and Slack QA reference](#telegram-discord-and-slack-qa-reference) below.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:156:| Telegram | x      | x              | x          |                 |                 |                |                  |                  |                      | x            |                             |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:161:Telegram, and future live transports share one explicit transport-contract\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:185:## Telegram, Discord, and Slack QA reference\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:187:Matrix has a [dedicated page](/concepts/qa-matrix) because of its scenario count and Docker-backed homeserver provisioning. Telegram, Discord, and Slack are smaller — a handful of scenarios each, no profile system, against pre-existing real channels — so their reference lives here.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:196:| `--output-dir <path>`                 | `<repo>/.artifacts/qa-e2e/{telegram,discord,slack}-<timestamp>` | Where reports/summary/observed messages and the output log are written. Relative paths resolve against `--repo-root`. |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:207:### Telegram QA\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:210:pnpm openclaw qa telegram\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:213:Targets one real private Telegram group with two distinct bots (driver + SUT). The SUT bot must have a Telegram username; bot-to-bot observation works best when both bots have **Bot-to-Bot Communication Mode** enabled in `@BotFather`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:225:Scenarios (`extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/telegram/telegram-live.runtime.ts:44`):\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:227:- `telegram-canary`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:228:- `telegram-mention-gating`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:229:- `telegram-mentioned-message-reply`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:230:- `telegram-help-command`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:231:- `telegram-commands-command`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:232:- `telegram-tools-compact-command`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:233:- `telegram-whoami-command`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:234:- `telegram-context-command`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:235:- `telegram-long-final-reuses-preview`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:236:- `telegram-long-final-three-chunks`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:240:- `telegram-qa-report.md`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:241:- `telegram-qa-summary.json` — includes per-reply RTT (driver send → observed SUT reply) starting with the canary.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:242:- `telegram-qa-observed-messages.json` — bodies redacted unless `OPENCLAW_QA_TELEGRAM_CAPTURE_CONTENT=1`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:495:Telegram, Discord, and Slack lanes can lease credentials from a shared Convex pool instead of reading the env vars above. Pass `--credential-source convex` (or set `OPENCLAW_QA_CREDENTIAL_SOURCE=convex`); QA Lab acquires an exclusive lease, heartbeats it for the duration of the run, and releases it on shutdown. Pool kinds are `\"telegram\"`, `\"discord\"`, and `\"slack\"`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:499:- Telegram (`kind: \"telegram\"`): `{ groupId: string, driverToken: string, sutToken: string }` — `groupId` must be a numeric chat-id string.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/qa-e2e-automation.md:503:Operational env vars and the Convex broker endpoint contract live in [Testing → Shared Telegram credentials via Convex](/help/testing#shared-telegram-credentials-via-convex-v1) (the section name predates Discord support; the broker semantics are identical for both kinds).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/markdown-formatting.md:20:- **Channel fit:** map the same IR to Slack mrkdwn, Telegram HTML, and Signal\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/markdown-formatting.md:34:   - **Telegram:** HTML tags (`<b>`, `<i>`, `<s>`, `<code>`, `<pre><code>`, `<a href>`).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/markdown-formatting.md:57:- Slack, Telegram, and Signal outbound adapters render from the IR.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/markdown-formatting.md:101:- **Telegram:** `[label](url)` -> `<a href=\"url\">label</a>` (HTML parse mode).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/markdown-formatting.md:125:- Telegram HTML requires escaping text outside tags to avoid broken markup.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/channel-docking.md:5:  - You want replies for one active session to move from Telegram to Discord, Slack, Mattermost, or another linked channel\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/channel-docking.md:17:Alice can message OpenClaw on Telegram and Discord:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/channel-docking.md:23:      alice: [\"telegram:123\", \"discord:456\"],\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/channel-docking.md:29:If Alice sends this from Telegram:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/channel-docking.md:39:| Replies go to Telegram `123` | Replies go to Discord `456` |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/channel-docking.md:51:1. Start an agent task from Telegram.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/channel-docking.md:53:3. Send `/dock_discord` from the Telegram session."}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778719985080}}
