{"type":"message","id":"a351558e","parentId":"252cad96","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:56:22.626Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_JBXPJWUM5Ju23hHtOrEE4uOz|fc_094b6994f4566fc6016a051daac7508194b189f641b5ed5396","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/architecture.md:52:- In remote setups, connects through the same SSH/Tailscale tunnel as other\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/architecture.md:87:- Identity-bearing modes such as Tailscale Serve\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/architecture.md:88:  (`gateway.auth.allowTailscale: true`) or non-loopback\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/architecture.md:127:- Preferred: Tailscale or VPN.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/architecture.md:128:- Alternative: SSH tunnel\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/architecture.md:134:- The same handshake + auth token apply over the tunnel.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/presence.md:81:## Remote/tunnel caveat (loopback IPs)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/presence.md:83:When a client connects over an SSH tunnel / local port forward, the Gateway may\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:193:Create a service account and enable domain-wide delegation in the Admin Console.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:206:Domain-wide delegation allows the service account to impersonate **any user in the entire domain**. Restrict the scopes to the minimum required, and limit the service account's client ID to only the scopes listed above in the Admin Console (Security > API controls > Domain-wide delegation). A leaked service account key with broad scopes grants full access to every mailbox and calendar in the organization. Rotate keys on a schedule and monitor the Admin Console audit log for unexpected impersonation events.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/exec-approvals-advanced.md:243:Microsoft Teams in addition to the existing Web UI and terminal UI flows.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/browser.md:488:- Tailscale Serve identity headers and `gateway.auth.mode: \"trusted-proxy\"` do\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/browser.md:494:- Keep the Gateway and any node hosts on a private network (Tailscale); avoid public exposure.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/capability-cookbook.md:17:Use this when OpenClaw needs a new domain such as image generation, video\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/web.md:88:    Structured results with content extraction controls and domain filtering.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/web.md:111:| [Perplexity](/tools/perplexity-search)    | Structured snippets                                            | Country, language, time, domains, content limits | `PERPLEXITY_API_KEY` / `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`                                             |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/web.md:316:| `domain_filter`       | Domain allowlist/denylist array (Perplexity only)     |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/web.md:437:  domain_filter: [\"-reddit.com\", \"-pinterest.com\"],\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/perplexity-search.md:130:<ParamField path=\"domain_filter\" type=\"string[]\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/perplexity-search.md:148:  `date_before`, `domain_filter`, `max_tokens`, and `max_tokens_per_page`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/perplexity-search.md:177:  domain_filter: [\"nature.com\", \"science.org\", \".edu\"],\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/perplexity-search.md:183:  domain_filter: [\"-reddit.com\", \"-pinterest.com\"],\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/perplexity-search.md:196:- Maximum 20 domains per filter\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/brave-search.md:140:- [Perplexity Search](/tools/perplexity-search) -- structured results with domain filtering\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents-setup.md:249:- Keeps core-tool exposure explicit and default-off.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tavily.md:18:filtering, domain filters, AI-generated answer summaries, and content extraction\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tavily.md:61:  or domain filters, use `tavily_search`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tavily.md:78:| `include_domains` | Array of domains to restrict results to                               |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tavily.md:79:| `exclude_domains` | Array of domains to exclude from results                              |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/gemini-search.md:93:`timeRangeFilter`. `country`, `language`, and `domain_filter` are not supported.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/browser-control.md:45:  Tailscale Serve identity headers.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/browser-control.md:359:- Remote CDP endpoints are powerful; tunnel and protect them.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/diffs.md:469:    - If `gateway.trustedProxies` includes loopback for a same-host proxy (for example Tailscale Serve), raw loopback viewer requests without forwarded client-IP headers fail closed by design.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/exa-search.md:152:- [Perplexity Search](/tools/perplexity-search) -- structured results with domain filtering\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq-first-run.md:121:    - **Tailscale Serve** (recommended): keep bind loopback, run `openclaw gateway --tailscale serve`, open `https://<magicdns>/`. If `gateway.auth.allowTailscale` is `true`, identity headers satisfy Control UI/WebSocket auth (no pasted shared secret, assumes trusted gateway host); HTTP APIs still require shared-secret auth unless you deliberately use private-ingress `none` or trusted-proxy HTTP auth.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq-first-run.md:125:    - **SSH tunnel**: `ssh -N -L 18789:127.0.0.1:18789 user@host` then open `http://127.0.0.1:18789/`. Shared-secret auth still applies over the tunnel; paste the configured token or password if prompted.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq-first-run.md:207:    If the Gateway is remote, ensure the tunnel/Tailscale connection is up and that the UI\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq-first-run.md:446:    Any Linux VPS works. Install on the server, then use SSH/Tailscale to reach the Gateway.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq-first-run.md:462:    from your laptop/phone via the Control UI (or Tailscale/SSH). Your state + workspace\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:358:    Run the Gateway where the macOS binaries exist, then connect from Linux in [remote mode](#gateway-ports-already-running-and-remote-mode) or over Tailscale. The skills load normally because the Gateway host is macOS.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:692:    - Shared-secret Control UI setups authenticate via `connect.params.auth.token` or `connect.params.auth.password` (stored in app/UI settings). Identity-bearing modes such as Tailscale Serve or `trusted-proxy` use request headers instead. Avoid putting shared secrets in URLs.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:896:    3. Ensure the Gateway WS is reachable (tailnet bind or SSH tunnel).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:915:  <Accordion title=\"Tailscale is connected but I get no replies. What now?\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:924:    - If you use Tailscale Serve, make sure `gateway.auth.allowTailscale` is set correctly.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:925:    - If you connect via SSH tunnel, confirm the local tunnel is up and points at the right port.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:928:    Docs: [Tailscale](/gateway/tailscale), [Remote access](/gateway/remote), [Channels](/channels).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:942:    via SSH/Tailscale (see [Remote access](/gateway/remote)).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1018:  <Accordion title=\"How do I set up Tailscale on a VPS and connect from my Mac?\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1029:       - Use the Tailscale app and sign in to the same tailnet.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1031:       - In the Tailscale admin console, enable MagicDNS so the VPS has a stable name.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1036:    If you want the Control UI without SSH, use Tailscale Serve on the VPS:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1042:    This keeps the gateway bound to loopback and exposes HTTPS via Tailscale. See [Tailscale](/gateway/tailscale).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1046:  <Accordion title=\"How do I connect a Mac node to a remote Gateway (Tailscale Serve)?\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1053:       The app will tunnel the Gateway port and connect as a node.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1468:    - If remote, tunnel first: `ssh -N -L 18789:127.0.0.1:18789 user@host` then open `http://127.0.0.1:18789/`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1470:    - Tailscale Serve mode: make sure `gateway.auth.allowTailscale` is enabled and you are opening the Serve URL, not a raw loopback/tailnet URL that bypasses Tailscale identity headers.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1483:    `tailnet` bind picks a Tailscale IP from your network interfaces (100.64.0.0/10). If the machine isn't on Tailscale (or the interface is down), there's nothing to bind to.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1487:    - Start Tailscale on that host (so it has a 100.x address), or\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1524:    - A proxy or tunnel stripped auth headers or sent a non-Gateway request.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1637:    If you are remote, confirm the tunnel/Tailscale connection is up and that the\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1650:    4. If remote, is the tunnel/Tailscale link up?\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/testing-live.md:209:- Goal: tunnel through a local HTTP CONNECT proxy to Apple's sandbox APNs endpoint, send the APNs HTTP/2 validation request, and assert Apple's real `403 InvalidProviderToken` response comes back through the proxy path.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/troubleshooting.md:162:    - On the async Tailscale Serve Control UI path, failed attempts for the same\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/testing.md:631:- Container smoke runners: `test:docker:openwebui`, `test:docker:onboard`, `test:docker:npm-onboard-channel-agent`, `test:docker:update-channel-switch`, `test:docker:upgrade-survivor`, `test:docker:published-upgrade-survivor`, `test:docker:session-runtime-context`, `test:docker:agents-delete-shared-workspace`, `test:docker:gateway-network`, `test:docker:browser-cdp-snapshot`, `test:docker:mcp-channels`, `test:docker:pi-bundle-mcp-tools`, `test:docker:cron-mcp-cleanup`, `test:docker:plugins`, `test:docker:plugin-update`, `test:docker:plugin-lifecycle-matrix`, and `test:docker:config-reload` boot one or more real containers and verify higher-level integration paths.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/testing.md:641:- Open WebUI live smoke: `pnpm test:docker:openwebui` (script: `scripts/e2e/openwebui-docker.sh`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/testing.md:686:`test:docker:openwebui` is a higher-level compatibility smoke: it starts an\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/network.md:25:- **Remote access** is typically SSH tunnel or Tailscale VPN ([Remote Access](/gateway/remote)).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/network.md:55:- [Tailscale](/gateway/tailscale)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/incident-response.md:30:- **Critical:** Package/release/repository compromise, active exploitation, or unauthenticated trust-boundary bypass with high-impact control or data exposure.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/incident-response.md:31:- **High:** Verified trust-boundary bypass requiring limited preconditions (for example authenticated but unauthorized high-impact action), or exposure of OpenClaw-owned sensitive credentials.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/incident-response.md:53:- Low-risk hardening findings may be documented in release notes or advisories without CVE, depending on impact and user exposure.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/THREAT-MODEL-ATLAS.md:84:│  │  • Token/Password/Tailscale auth                          │   │\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/THREAT-MODEL-ATLAS.md:158:| **Current Mitigations** | Tailscale auth option, bind to loopback by default                   |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/THREAT-MODEL-ATLAS.md:208:| **Attack Vector**       | Malware, unauthorized device access, config backup exposure |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/formal-verification.md:54:### Gateway exposure and open gateway misconfiguration\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/formal-verification.md:56:**Claim:** binding beyond loopback without auth can make remote compromise possible / increases exposure; token/password blocks unauth attackers (per the model assumptions).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/formal-verification.md:59:  - `make gateway-exposure-v2`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/formal-verification.md:60:  - `make gateway-exposure-v2-protected`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/formal-verification.md:62:  - `make gateway-exposure-v2-negative`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/formal-verification.md:64:See also: `docs/gateway-exposure-matrix.md` in the models repo.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/network-proxy.md:102:- Apply policy at connect time for both plain HTTP requests and HTTPS `CONNECT` tunnels.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/network-proxy.md:116:| `127.0.0.0/8`, `localhost`, `localhost.localdomain`                                  | IPv4 loopback                                        |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/network-proxy.md:143:By default, when no custom destinations are provided, the command checks that `https://example.com/` succeeds and starts a temporary loopback canary that the proxy must not reach. The default denied check passes when the proxy returns a non-2xx denial response or blocks the canary with a transport failure; it fails if a successful response reaches the canary. If no proxy is enabled and configured, validation reports a config problem; use `--proxy-url` for a one-off preflight before changing config. Use `--allowed-url` and `--denied-url` to test deployment-specific expectations. Add `--apns-reachable` to also verify direct APNs HTTP/2 delivery can open a CONNECT tunnel through the proxy and receive a sandbox APNs response; the probe uses an intentionally invalid provider token, so `403 InvalidProviderToken` is expected and counts as reachable. Custom denied destinations are fail-closed: any HTTP response means the destination was reachable through the proxy, and any transport error is reported as inconclusive because OpenClaw cannot prove the proxy blocked a reachable origin. On validation failure, the command exits with code 1.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/security/network-proxy.md:204:- The local debug proxy is diagnostic tooling and its direct upstream forwarding for proxy requests and CONNECT tunnels is disabled by default while managed proxy mode is active; enable direct forwarding only for approved local diagnostics.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/digitalocean.md:119:**Option B: Tailscale Serve (HTTPS, loopback-only)**\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/digitalocean.md:126:# Configure Gateway to use Tailscale Serve\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/platforms/digitalocean.md:135:- Serve keeps the Gateway loopback-only and authenticates Control UI/WebSocket traffic via Tailscale identity headers (tokenless auth assumes trusted gateway host; HTTP APIs do not use those Tailscale headers and instead follow the gateway's normal HTTP auth mode).[... 5916 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778720182625}}
