{"type":"message","id":"9f9feac5","parentId":"663e55ce","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:13:02.111Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_lMjzZgsNpvBKh8psXye5q5tK|fc_094b6994f4566fc6016a05219c74a881948ba573404e83f857","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/progress-drafts.md:183:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session-pruning.md:73:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-workspace.md:15:The workspace is the **default cwd**, not a hard sandbox. Tools resolve relative paths against the workspace, but absolute paths can still reach elsewhere on the host unless sandboxing is enabled. If you need isolation, use [`agents.defaults.sandbox`](/gateway/sandboxing) (and/or per-agent sandbox config).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-workspace.md:28:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-workspace.md:45:{ agents: { defaults: { skipBootstrap: true } } }\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-workspace.md:110:- `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth-profiles.json` (model auth profiles: OAuth + API keys)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-workspace.md:111:- `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/codex-home/` (per-agent Codex runtime account, config, skills, plugins, and native thread state)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-workspace.md:113:- `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/` (session transcripts + metadata)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-workspace.md:216:    If you need sessions, copy `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/` from the old machine separately.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/openclaw-sdk.md:32:| `oc.agents`               | Ready  | Lists, creates, updates, deletes, and gets agent handles.                  |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/openclaw-sdk.md:132:  agentId: \"main\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/openclaw-sdk.md:163:  agentId?: string;\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/commitments.md:81:created. A follow-up inferred while talking to one agent in Discord is not\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-runtimes.md:48:| Codex ACP adapter                                    | `runtime: \"acp\"`, `agentId: \"codex\"`       | Runs Codex through the external ACP/acpx control plane. Use only when ACP/acpx is explicitly asked.        |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-runtimes.md:63:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-runtimes.md:96:   ACP with `runtime: \"acp\"` and `agentId: \"codex\"`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-runtimes.md:156:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/features.md:17:  <Card title=\"Routing\" icon=\"route\" href=\"/concepts/multi-agent\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-builtin.md:29:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-builtin.md:47:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-builtin.md:81:- **Index location:** `~/.openclaw/memory/<agentId>.sqlite`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/parallel-specialist-lanes.md:8:  - You are designing a multi-agent operations setup\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/parallel-specialist-lanes.md:57:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/parallel-specialist-lanes.md:60:      subagents: { maxConcurrent: 8 },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/parallel-specialist-lanes.md:125:- [Multi-agent routing](/concepts/multi-agent)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:11:An **agent** here is the full per-persona scope: workspace files, auth profiles, model registry, and session store. `agentDir` is the on-disk state directory that holds this per-agent config at `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/`. A **binding** maps a channel account (e.g. a Slack workspace or a WhatsApp number) to one of those agents.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:19:- **Session store** (chat history + routing state) under `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:24:~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth-profiles.json\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:52:- Workspace: `~/.openclaw/workspace` (or `~/.openclaw/workspace-<agentId>`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:53:- Agent dir: `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent` (or `agents.list[].agentDir`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:54:- Sessions: `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:60:- `agentId` defaults to **`main`**.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:92:    Each agent gets its own workspace with `SOUL.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and optional `USER.md`, plus a dedicated `agentDir` and session store under `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:123:With **multiple agents**, each `agentId` becomes a **fully isolated persona**:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:137:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:180:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:188:      agentId: \"alex\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:192:      agentId: \"mia\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:269:- `agentId`: one \"brain\" (workspace, per-agent auth, per-agent session store).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:271:- `binding`: routes inbound messages to an `agentId` by `(channel, accountId, peer)` and optionally guild/team ids.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:272:- Direct chats collapse to `agent:<agentId>:<mainKey>` (per-agent \"main\"; `session.mainKey`).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:282:      agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:289:        { agentId: \"main\", match: { channel: \"discord\", accountId: \"default\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:290:        { agentId: \"coding\", match: { channel: \"discord\", accountId: \"coding\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:329:      agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:336:        { agentId: \"main\", match: { channel: \"telegram\", accountId: \"default\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:337:        { agentId: \"alerts\", match: { channel: \"telegram\", accountId: \"alerts\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:373:      agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:393:        { agentId: \"home\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"personal\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:394:        { agentId: \"work\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"biz\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:398:          agentId: \"work\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:443:      agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:460:        { agentId: \"chat\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:461:        { agentId: \"opus\", match: { channel: \"telegram\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:477:      agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:495:          agentId: \"opus\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:498:        { agentId: \"chat\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:511:      agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:542:          agentId: \"family\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:566:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:611:See [Multi-agent sandbox and tools](/tools/multi-agent-sandbox-tools) for detailed examples.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:117:`agents.defaults`, not the root config.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory.md:101:multi-agent awareness. Plugin install.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/oauth.md:59:- Auth profiles (OAuth + API keys + optional value-level refs): `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth-profiles.json`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/oauth.md:60:- Legacy compatibility file: `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth.json`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/experimental-features.md:27:| Memory search            | `agents.defaults.memorySearch.experimental.sessionMemory` | You want `memory_search` to index prior session transcripts and accept the extra storage/indexing cost         | [Memory configuration reference](/reference/memory-config#session-memory-search-experimental) |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/experimental-features.md:62:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-failover.md:72:- Secrets live in `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth-profiles.json` (legacy: `~/.openclaw/agent/auth-profiles.json`).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-failover.md:73:- Runtime auth-routing state lives in `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth-state.json`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-failover.md:91:Profiles live in `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth-profiles.json` under `profiles`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/compaction.md:123:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent.md:25:## Bootstrap files (injected)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent.md:47:{ agents: { defaults: { skipBootstrap: true } } }\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent.md:80:- `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/<SessionId>.jsonl`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent.md:137:- [Multi-agent routing](/concepts/multi-agent)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/active-memory.md:35:          agents: [\"main\"],\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/active-memory.md:67:- `config.agents: [\"main\"]` opts only the `main` agent into active memory\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/active-memory.md:523:          agents: [\"main\"],\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/active-memory.md:605:          agents: [\"main\"],\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session.md:95:- **Store:** `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/sessions.json`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session.md:96:- **Transcripts:** `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/<sessionId>.jsonl`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session.md:150:- [Multi-Agent](/concepts/multi-agent) — routing and session isolation across agents\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-loop.md:169:- Model idle timeout: OpenClaw aborts a model request when no response chunks arrive before the idle window. `models.providers.<id>.timeoutSeconds` extends this idle watchdog for slow local/self-hosted providers; otherwise OpenClaw uses `agents.defaults.timeoutSeconds` when configured, capped at 120s by default. Cron-triggered runs with no explicit model or agent timeout disable the idle watchdog and rely on the cron outer timeout.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/timezone.md:25:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/timezone.md:78:  agents: { defaults: { userTimezone: \"America/Chicago\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:24:    `openclaw configure` preserves an existing `agents.defaults.model.primary` when you add or reauth a provider. Provider plugins may still return a recommended default model in their auth config patch, but configure treats that as \"make this model available\" when a primary model already exists, not \"replace the current primary model.\"\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:107:  agents: { defaults: { model: { primary: \"openai/gpt-5.5\" } } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:130:  agents: { defaults: { model: { primary: \"anthropic/claude-opus-4-6\" } } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:157:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:202:  agents: { defaults: { model: { primary: \"opencode/claude-opus-4-6\" } } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:375:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:403:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:422:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:462:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:500:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:552:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:576:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:602:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:628:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:642:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:711:- [Configuration reference](/gateway/config-agents#agent-defaults) — model config keys\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/system-prompt.md:146:Bootstrap files are trimmed and appended under **Project Context** so the model sees identity and profile context without needing explicit reads:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/system-prompt.md:222:`agents.list[].skills` is configured.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session-tool.md:48:`sessions_list` returns sessions with their key, agentId, kind, channel, model,\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session-tool.md:50:`node`), exact `label`, exact `agentId`, search text, or recency\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session-tool.md:181:- [Multi-agent](/concepts/multi-agent) -- multi-agent architecture\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:43:`~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/qmd/` and manages the sidecar lifecycle\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:10:This extends [Multi-Agent Routing](/concepts/multi-agent) from personal use into organizational deployments.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:124:See [Sandboxing](/gateway/sandboxing) and [Multi-Agent Sandbox & Tools](/tools/multi-agent-sandbox-tools).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:142:Use the multi-agent wizard to create an isolated agent for the delegate:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:211:Route inbound messages to the delegate agent using [Multi-Agent Routing](/concepts/multi-agent) bindings:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:215:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:230:      agentId: \"delegate\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:235:      agentId: \"delegate\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:239:    { agentId: \"main\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:246:Copy or create auth profiles for the delegate's `agentDir`:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:253:Never share the main agent's `agentDir` with the delegate. See [Multi-Agent Routing](/concepts/multi-agent) for auth isolation details.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:261:  agents: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:279:      agentId: \"org-assistant\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:282:    { agentId: \"org-assistant\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"org\" } },[... 12894 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778721182110}}
